others.name: Mouse
others.package_description: Please note: In general you do not have to concern yourself with these methods. The methods here will be called from interact methods by the API (such as the interact method in RectangleDestination )

others.name: KeyboardEvent
others.package_description:
Event to handle typing messages on the keyboard
 Uses the implementation of Keyboard.getKeyboardTypingAlgorithm() Automatically stops if script is stopped or paused when no random solver is active.

others.name: KeyEventGenerator
others.package_description: Generates a KeyEvent using the given information.

enums.name: Key
enums.package_description:
Enum representing the possible keys to press
 Alphabet will automatically adjust to upper/lowercase based on whether shift is currently being held if you use Key.getChar()

others.name: DBKeyEvent
others.package_description:
Represents a DreamBot implementation of KeyEvent Will set the internal fields required for a key event to emulate a system level event
 Primarily for internal use, please see implementations of AbstractKeyEvent for sending keyboard events

others.name: AbstractKeyEvent
others.package_description: Abstract key event class to clean up implementations

others.name: HoldKey
others.package_description:
Event to handle holding a key
 Does not create a new thread on its own, you must put this call inside a thread if you require it to be threaded.

others.name: PressKey
others.package_description:
Creates a KeyEvent.KEY_PRESSED event
 Marks the key as pressed internally and marks the last key location that was used for the press on that key where available

others.name: ReleaseKey
others.package_description:
Creates a KeyEvent.KEY_RELEASED event
 Marks the key as released internally
 Resets the last key location used to press this key
 If no location is passed in for this event, it will default to either the key's default location or the last pressed location

others.name: TypeKey
others.package_description:
Creates a KeyEvent.KEY_TYPED event
 Does NOT handle press or release events.

enums.name: MouseButton
enums.package_description:
Mouse button to use when clicking
 Using NULL will mean it will not click

enums.name: MouseMode
enums.package_description:
Mode to use for MouseEvent s
 Note: If you want the mouse to do the full press, release, click series of events, use the mode MouseMode.FULL_CLICK Mode NONE will do only mouse movement.

enums.name: WheelMode
enums.package_description: Wheel mode for whether to scroll up or down

others.name: MouseEvent
others.package_description: Mouse event that handles the full movement and click process based on the fields you pass in.

others.name: MouseEventGenerator
others.package_description: Utility class to generate a MouseEvent for the given parameters.

others.name: DBMouseEvent
others.package_description:
DreamBot implementation of MouseEvent Sets all required internal fields
 Primarily used internally, you should be using AbstractMouseEvent implementations for sending mouse events

others.name: DBMouseWheelEvent
others.package_description:
DreamBot implementation of MouseWheelEvent Sets all required internal fields
 Primarily used internally, you should be using AbstractMouseEvent implementations for sending mouse events
 Sets abs x/y to 0 as expected, if your OS/JVM behaves differently please report your OS and JVM to one of the developers so we can research it in more depth

others.name: AbstractMouseEvent
others.package_description: Abstract class for sending mouse events

others.name: ClickEvent
others.package_description:
Sends a MouseEvent.MOUSE_CLICKED event
 Removes this mouse button from mouse modifiers
 Does NOT handle press/release events

others.name: ExitEvent
others.package_description:
creates and sends a MouseEvent.MOUSE_EXITED event
 Sets DreamBot's Mouse.setPosition(int, int) to -1,-1
 Destination point does NOT get altered

others.name: MoveEvent
others.package_description:
Creates and sends a MouseEvent.MOUSE_MOVED or MouseEvent.MOUSE_DRAGGED if Mouse.getCurrentModifiers() is not 0
 If hop is set to true, event will emulate a touch screen event
 Sets Mouse.setPosition(int, int) to the destination x/y

others.name: PressEvent
others.package_description: Creates and sends a MouseEvent.MOUSE_PRESSED event using the given MouseButton Marks the relevant modifiers to Mouse.addModifierFromClick(MouseButton)

others.name: ReleaseEvent
others.package_description:
Creates and sends a MouseEvent.MOUSE_RELEASED event
 Marks the relevant modifiers to Mouse.addModifierFromClick(MouseButton) Note: Press and Release ADD to the modifier, ClickEvent removes the modifier post-event
 If MouseButton.RIGHT_CLICK is used, it will adjust the event to be a popup trigger

others.name: WheelEvent
others.package_description: Creates and sends a MouseEvent.MOUSE_WHEEL event based on the given WheelMode
